Privacy Policy
Last updated: Aug 23, 2025

usDrive ("the Service") respects your privacy. This document explains what information we collect and how we handle it.

1. Information We Collect
- When you sign in using Google OAuth, we receive your basic profile information (such as your email, name and profile picture).
- We may store files you upload to the Service.

2. How We Use Information
- To provide the Service (e.g., managing uploads and authentication).
- To maintain and improve the Service.

3. What We Do NOT Do
- We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal data with third parties.
- We do not use your data for advertising purposes.

4. Sharing of Information
- We only share information if required by law or to protect our rights.
- Files you upload are only accessible to you unless you explicitly share them.

5. Data Security
- We take reasonable measures to protect your data, but we cannot guarantee absolute security as this project is a hobby Open Source project licensed under MIT LICENSE.

6. Your Choices
- You may delete your files from the Service at any time.
- If you want your account and associated data deleted, contact us at adistrim@duck.com.

7. Changes
- We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If changes are significant, we will notify users by updating the date above.

Contact
If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please reach us at adistrim@duck.com.
